main event: A witness reported seeing a round, green object with a spark trail upon disappearance sinking into the horizon towards the west.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3 minutes.
Scientists at the Smithsonian Astrophysical Observatory reported an extremely bright meteor in the observer's area at the time of the sighting.
The Air Force requested the witness to complete an AF Form 164 to provide more information for evaluation, but the form was not received within 30 days.
The conclusion was that there was insufficient data to evaluate the sighting.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were described as clear with 18 degrees temperature and 2 knots wind speed.
sighted object: round, green object with a spark trail
